A powerful app for interactive & experimental digital media artists. Send sensor data, share camera feeds, and control phone hardware utilising OSC and Spout.
Download
About SeeOSC
SeeOSC was built from the ground up for digital artists who want to blur the lines between physical and virtual worlds. By leveraging OSC, you can send sensor data from your phone—accelerometer, gyroscope, touch coordinates etc, all while sending a Spout and receiving video streams output via Spout in real-time.
Create live visuals projected on-stage, all controlled by the tilt of a performer’s phone, prototype and develop interfaces rendered by a remote system, or create immersive interactive experiences driven by the camera and sensors of a mobile device. The possibilities are endless.
Features
Sensor Data via OSC
Send a plethora sensor data from your phone for real-time visuals and audio manipulation.
Video Streaming
Send a camera feed and receive a video stream - create powerful visuals offloaded from the phone's hardware
Custom Control Surface
Create a custom control surface to send OSC, MIDI or DMX, while also sending sensor data
Phone Hardware Control
Receive OSC commands to change screen brightness, vibration, and other device settings.
Web-Based Config
Access and configure app settings from any browser on the local network—no more tiny menus.
Handy Extras
Send dummy sensor data to free your hands and transmit device info for convenient programming.
Display Options
Choose to either display an incoming video stream, a local image/video or a blank screen when sending sensor data.
Industry Standard Protocols
Utilises OSC for sharing sensor data and Spout for incoming and outgoing video streams.
Easy to Use
Streamlined user-interface with helpful tooltips for every setting.
In Action
See how SeeOSC can be used in a live performance setting.
